narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Awesome class, everyone should take it.
A continuation of PORT 110; would recommend!

PORT 120 fills in the grammatical gaps from PORT 110. You finish Bom Dia, Brasil and have a good grip on most of the topics it presents. Semester is a little light on vocabulary, a little heavy on grammar.
Great class. It's fun and you actually learn a lot of the language and about Brazil.

Portuguese at Yale is great. It's a pretty chill department, so the classes tend to be fun and they don't require a lot of work. All the professors are good, and you learn a lot without feeling very stressed out. You especially learn a lot without very much work if you are a native Spanish speaker.
